Combine the currants and rum in a small bowl and let stand until soft, about 30 minutes. Melt the butter in a small skillet over medium heat. Add the corn and saut√© until soft, about 2 minutes. Stir in the currants and soaking liquid, pine nuts, citron, lemon zest, sugar, cinnamon, and vanilla extract. Bring to a boil, then remove the pan from the heat. Correct the flavorings, adding sugar or spices to taste.